        "description": "<div>Barrel is a creative and digital marketing agency founded in 2006. We are a remote-first team with members across the world and offices in New York City and Los Angeles. </div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>We partner with the world’s most loved brands to scale and optimize their direct-to-consumer (DTC) businesses through brand, UX/design, technology/development, CRM/email, and marketing strategy. </div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Barrel specializes in the Fashion &amp; Apparel, CPG Food &amp; Beverage, Beauty &amp; Skincare and Home Goods verticals. We work with clients including L’Oreal Paris, Gap, Barry’s, ScottsMiracle-Gro &amp; Hu.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Barrel is looking for a Solutions Architect to join our remote-first team - you can work from anywhere in the US. </span> <span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">A Solutions Architect is responsible for estimating and scoping projects, technical project planning, and ensuring that projects are completed to specification within an established time frame and budget. A Solutions Architect is a subject matter expert within the company regarding technology related to full-stack web development, eCommerce, and content management.</span></div>\n<div> </div>\n<div><strong style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Responsibilities:</strong></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Analyze, plan and develop requirements and standards in reference to project plans</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Assign and oversee the daily tasks of technical personnel while ensuring all subordinates are actively working toward established milestones</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Research and evaluate software technology options and weigh the cost/benefit analysis when relying on third-party platforms, apps, plugins, services, etc.</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Conduct research and assist on new business estimating/scoping efforts</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Brainstorm and communicate technical solutions directly with clients in a courteous and professional manner</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Understand our clients needs and their businesses to best solve their challenges</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Ensure that correct technology processes are being employed and followed on projects</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Contribute to best practices, workflows, and standards and company knowledge sharing</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Present simple solutions and alternatives to complex and pricey problems</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Lead and oversee developers while assisting with execution on current projects with new tasks</span></div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">·</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Help the team write and improve automated and continuous integration, testing, release, and deployments</span></div>\n<p><br><br></p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Skills:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong web and Mac desktop skills – we use Microsoft Office, Google Docs, and various web-based tools such as Basecamp, Harvest, JIRA and Asana</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to communicate professionally with technical and non-technical colleagues and clientsAdvanced understanding of software technology, ability to break down complex problems/asks</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Proven ability to manage large scale technology projects successfully</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to effectively prioritize and execute tasks in a high-pressure environment</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong communication skills (both in person and in writing) while interacting with individuals with a range of technical understanding</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent organizational and time management skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><br></p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Experience:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Associates or Bachelor's degree in relevant field of Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology, and/or equivalent combination of education and work experience</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>4 + years of web development experience; prior experience working in a design or advertising agency is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Knowledge of Shopify, Headless and WordPress</li>\n</ul>\n<div>As a full-time member of the Barrel team, we offer the following benefits:</div>\n<div>- Remote Work</div>\n<div>- Competitive Salary</div>\n<div>- Health/dental/vision coverage</div>\n<div>- Paid vacation</div>\n<div>- Half-day Fridays all year round</div>\n<div>- Remote home setup stipend</div>\n<div>- Profit-sharing</div>\n<div>- 401k match</div>\n<div>- Professional development stipend</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Most importantly, we work on projects that truly impact our clients’ businesses and attract team members who love to be challenged with tough problems and fast-paced work.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Barrel is proud to be an equal opportunity employer dedicated to pursuing and hiring a diverse workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their race, color, culture, ethnicity, sex, gender identity and expression, nation of origin, age, veteran’s status, religion, disability, sexual orientation, appearance, opinions, beliefs and more.</div>\n"
