        "description": "<p>At Further, we help research and insight professionals do better, and more effective, qualitative research by providing them with a platform (‘Together') designed to help improve qual research and make it easier.</p>\n<p>Alongside our platform, we offer experienced research support, helpful guides and design templates (crafted by our Research Strategists) to make qualitative researchers lives easier and help them turn out amazing work as efficiently as possible.</p>\n<p>We have a truly impressive portfolio of clients, including Google, Colgate, Channel 4, Jaguar Land Rover and BUPA. Visit us at <a href=\"http://www.go-further.co\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.go-further.co</a></p>\n<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>\n<p>We are looking for a UI/UX specialist to join our Development team for 6 a month period (with extension possible). The development team consists of 2 senior developers and one junior developer who are supporting a legacy application, as well as a rebuild project.</p>\n<p>You will work with the two senior developers on the already implemented design of the rebuild application, which is split into two related SPAs with the goal of improving end user experience.</p>\n<p>We would like to see an extensive portfolio of your work, and you should be comfortable working within a team of developers.</p>\n<p><strong>Required Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vue JS (Minimum 2 years' experience)</li>\n<li>HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Minimum 4 years' experience)</li>\n<li>SASS (Minimum 3 years' experience)</li>\n<li>Bootstrap / Vue Bootstrap (Minimum 4 years' experience)</li>\n<li>GIT Experience (Minimum 2 years' experience)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Desired Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Worked with charts (preferably amCharts)</li>\n<li>Worked with drag and drop</li>\n<li>Asset handling (Video, images, audio)</li>\n<li>ESlint Experience</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nice to Have, not necessary skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vuex Experience</li>\n<li>Vue Router Experience</li>\n<li>i18n Experience</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Working Arrangement - </strong>Remote, but must be available to meet other developers on site in London (with at least 2 weeks notice)</p>\n<p><strong>Recommended Start - </strong>As soon as possible</p>\n"
