        "description": "<p><strong>ABOUT ANKR</strong></p>\n<p>Ankr offers node solutions for over 40 different chains and a “1 click” API service for Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, Polygon, Avalanche and more. Your primary mission is to help usher in developers into the web3 ecosystem. To do this, you’ll pioneer new solutions to solve some of the most pressing problems across decentralized systems and the DeFi movement, making multi-chain development easy.</p>\n<p>Ankr is hiring a Sr Product Manager, Developer Tools to lead our web3 developer experience. This position reports directly to our Head of Product, who is based in San Francisco. You’ll work closely with our CTO (ex-Amazon Web Services and Alexa lead), global engineering, developer advocacy, product marketing, and UX design teams to accomplish this mission.</p>\n<p>If you're passionate about great developer experiences and want to dive deep into the web3 ecosystem, this is an excellent opportunity to do both as you’ll work with Ankr’s existing customers and partners, including some of the most well known projects in the space.</p>\n<p>The ideal candidate has an engineering background and is looking to pivot into product management or a product manager with existing experience building developer experiences, tools, or API’s.</p>\n<p><strong>You will:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Build on top of ethereum virtual machine (EVM) compatible API calls to simplify building common use cases in the web3 and DeFI ecosystem</li>\n<li>Help lead partnerships and integrations with other blockchain service providers who add value to the developer experience</li>\n<li>Contribute to an upcoming blockchain protocol design and go-to-market</li>\n<li>Partner with product leadership on platform vision and strategy</li>\n<li>Develop relationships with web3 developers, contributing to customer and market research</li>\n<li>Have domain expertise in developer platforms and CI/CD tools</li>\n<li>Have strong analytical skills to use data to support decision making</li>\n<li>Possess an experimental mindset and use metrics to back up assumptions and evaluate outcomes</li>\n<li>Require high attention to detail and proven ability to manage multiple, competing for priorities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Track record of developing projects as an engineer or leading product development as a product manager</li>\n<li>Familiarity with CLI / NPM best practices</li>\n<li>Enthusiasm for the web3 movement</li>\n<li>Empathy for developer challenges</li>\n<li>Basic understanding of smart contracts, tokenomics, consensus protocols etc.</li>\n<li>Comfortable leading and hosting live online discussions</li>\n<li>Great listener and communicator</li>\n<li>Bilingual or high fluency in English</li>\n</ul>\n"
