        "description": "<div class=\"h1\">Description</div>\n<p>This is a remote position.</p>\n<div>**Remote position** <br>Our client designs simple software that helps organization to be more efficient and optimize their potential. With more than 10,000 customers in around 100 countries, this organization has managed to be recognize as as a pioneer in technological solutions on the market. For more than fifteen years now, they have combined human resources and the Cloud to shape the organization of tomorrow. With their products, they have the privilege of helping tens of thousands of businesses to improve the way they work.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Job Description</div>\n<div>The Product Owner:</div>\n<div>-Will collaborate with internal stakeholders such as the Product Manager on product roadmaps.</div>\n<div>-Will be responsible for ensuring a product backlog so that it is visible, transparent and clear.</div>\n<div>-Will communicate product goals and requirements by capturing user needs and writing user stories.</div>\n<div>-Will have to “map” or map the dependencies to order the necessary development sequences and thus mitigate the obstacles that could have an impact on the success.</div>\n<div>-Prioritize efforts based on time constraints, business goals and overall strategy.</div>\n<div>-Will see to identify opportunities for product improvement and work with the software development team to find solutions.</div>\n<div>-Will oversee the development of the various product functionalities, identify and organize the stages of the next iteration.</div>\n<div>-Act as the market expert for the software development team.</div>\n<div>-Serve as the main contact to support relations between the teams and regularly validate the proposed prioritization with the responsible parties.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>What does the team you are going to join look like?</div>\n<div>By joining the company as Product Manager, you will work in tandem with two fabulous teams who contribute to the continued success of the product. It is by combining the vision: product management, a memorable user experience and technology, that year after year, that the organization positions itself as the software of choice for users of Teams and O365.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Our two teams:</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>The first consists of a product strategist and the other main product managers, it is with her that you will define the product objectives, the roadmap, etc.</div>\n<div>The second is your product development team, there is a product designer and five developers.</div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Requirements</div>\n<div>You think strategically and tactically.</div>\n<div>You have between 3 and 7 years of experience as a product manager or product owner; SaaS experience is a significant asset</div>\n<div>You plan initiatives in complete autonomy (roadmap, MVP, MMP ...) and their measurement (KPI, output, outcome ...).</div>\n<div>You have knowledge of user research, data analysis and industry intelligence.</div>\n<div>You use quantitative and qualitative data to support your decisions.</div>\n<div>You understand the issues related to a technological solution.</div>\n<div>You speak and understand English; some of your colleagues will be unilingual anglophone</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>Further information</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>It is an environment of constant trust and support. You will be able to express yourself, evolve and develop in a work environment that adapts to your needs. This client aspires to build a healthy and inclusive work environment. This is everyone's business.</div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Benefits</div>\n<div>Benefits</div>\n<div>A very competitive vacation program</div>\n<div>A competitive salary for the market</div>\n<div>An environment of innovation and learning</div>\n<div>Unparalleled flexibility in teleworking; 100% teleworking is possible and if you decide to go to the office for a week, or a month, you can.</div>\n<div>Flexible work shifts.</div>\n<div>The main office is located in Montreal; but we engage across Canada, whether you're in Halifax or Vancouver; you will not have to come to the main office; except for certain corporate events where all expenses will be paid.</div>\n<div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h1\">Skills</div>\n<p>You think strategically and tactically. You have between 3 and 7 years of experience as a product manager or product owner; SaaS experience is a significant asset You plan initiatives in complete autonomy (roadmap, MVP, MMP ...) and their measurement (KPI, output, outcome ...). You have knowledge of user research, data analysis and industry intelligence. You use quantitative and qualitative data to support your decisions. You understand the issues related to a technological solution. You speak and understand English; some of your colleagues will be unilingual anglophone Further information It is an environment of constant trust and support. You will be able to express yourself, evolve and develop in a work environment that adapts to your needs. This client aspires to build a healthy and inclusive work environment. This is everyone's business.</p>\n"
