        "description": "<br><br><div class=\"h3\">Company Description</div><p>Perry Street Software is Jack’d and SCRUFF. We are two of the world’s largest gay, bi, trans and queer social dating apps on iOS and Android. Our brands reach more than 20 million members worldwide so members can connect, meet and express themselves on a platform that prioritizes privacy and security.</p><p>Perry Street is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, genetic information, national origin, ancestry, medical condition, disability, marital status, caregiver status, pregnancy, citizenship, age, military or veteran status, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.</p><br><br><div class=\"h3\">Job Description</div><p>We are hiring experienced Full Stack Mobile developers for the Labs Team to help us build the next-generation version of SCRUFF and Jack’d. The Labs Team is a nimble, creative team of intrapreneurs that incubates innovative ideas, rapidly developing new products, services, and business models to help shape the future of Jack’d and SCRUFF. The ideal candidate challenges assumptions, intuitively uncovers patterns, and excels in both execution and vision. We are a small, agile company, so the ability to make an impact is significant. The position is permanent and full-time, and remote.</p><p><strong>What you'll do:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop with the latest technologies in evolving the architecture for current and future needs in order to develop innovative, consumer-facing mobile products, while supporting the product roadmap</li><li>Work in an agile team with Product, Design, Support, and Marketing to respond to our users needs</li><li>Help develop solutions end to end, from the design, to requirements, coding, refactoring, delivering, and maintenance</li><li>Be a good communicator with both a local and remote team</li></ul><br><br><div class=\"h3\">Qualifications</div><p><strong>Who you are:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in computer science, related field, or equivalent practical experience</li><li>Product-minded engineer who wants to understand why decisions are made, how people use the product, and love to be involved in making product decisions</li><li>3+ years of software development experience</li><li>1+ year of Android, iOS, or React Native app development experience</li><li>Experience using design and architecture patterns</li><li>Strong knowledge of Java and Kotlin with the Android SDK, or Swift with the iOS SDK</li><li>Experience using RxJava or ReactiveSwift</li><li>Maps out edge cases and protects against them</li></ul><br><br><div class=\"h3\">Additional Information</div><p>All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.</p>"
