        "description": "<p>Striim is pronounced “stream”, with two i’s for integration and intelligence. The company was founded in 2012 as WebAction, with a mission to help companies make data useful the instant it’s born.</p>\n<p>We're looking to add a second very senior, very technical writer. Can be 100% remote.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>* extensive experience writing developer docs, including some SQL</p>\n<p>* self-starter who can be highly productive with minimal supervision</p>\n<p>* confidence that you could have written most of the current documentation</p>\n<p>Plus experience with most of the following:</p>\n<p>* enterprise software</p>\n<p>* writing sysadmin / ops docs</p>\n<p>* figuring things out by playing with the product, reading source code, inspecting repository database schemas, and so on</p>\n<p>* experience with reuse across products and release versions: document- and topic-level versioning and reuse, variable sets, snippets, profiling</p>\n<p>* integrating UI strings / tooltips / inline help with doc content management</p>\n<p>* Jira or similar issue tracking</p>\n<p>* active listening during engineering meetings that may be 95% irrelevant to docs</p>\n<p>* API docs / OpenAPI / Swagger</p>\n<p>* DocBook, DITA, or similar structured authoring</p>\n<p>* Docker &amp; Kubernetes</p>\n<p>* documenting cloud deployment (customer-facing) and operations (internal)</p>\n<p>* documenting dual-mode application development (GUI and code)</p>\n<p>* multi-platform applications (Linux, Mac, Windows)</p>\n<p>* Paligo / Flare / RoboHelp / Oxygen or other topic-oriented authoring tools</p>\n<p>* creating self-guided online training</p>\n<p>Check out the current documentation:</p>\n<p><a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.striim.com/docs\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.striim.com/docs</a></p>\n<p>Check out a free evaluation version of the product:</p>\n<p>* local installation: <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://go2.striim.com/download-free-trial\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://go2.striim.com/download-free-trial</a></p>\n<p>* Docker Hub: <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://docs.striim.com/en/running-striim-using-docker.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://docs.striim.com/en/running-striim-using-do...</a></p>\n<p>* or search the AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud Platform marketplaces</p>\n"
