        "candidate_required_location": "USA Only",
        "salary": "",
        "description": "<p><strong>Why Fyllo</strong></p><p>The economies of tomorrow are highly regulated today -- that's where we come in. Fyllo enables highly regulated companies to conquer compliance at scale, empowering our customers with the confidence to grow boldly. The first vertical we are tackling is cannabis.</p>\n<p>As a first mover, our pioneering technology makes compliance at scale possible in the fragmented cannabis industry. Having been founded in 2019, we're currently in Series B and have raised 60 million to date. Moving forward, we see the opportunity to enter many additional verticals that suffer from similar constraints. This is just the beginning! Come join us as we continue to innovate for a better way.</p>\n<p><br></p><p><strong>Your Role</strong></p>\n<p>Fyllo Support team is looking for a customer-obsessed team member who is engaged, courteous and who will partner with our Retails Solutions customers from start to finish to resolve their concerns. As a Technical Support Specialist, you will work with several teams within the company, ensuring all service level agreements and customer satisfaction goals are achieved. This is a perfect opportunity for someone who loves working in fast-paced startup environments and wants to help blaze the trail for future growth. This position requires organized, strategic, and proactive thinking.<br><br></p>\n<p><strong>Day to Day</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Provide best-in-class service to all end-users in a courteous professional manner via telephone, email and service desk tickets</li><li>Coordinate and perform installation on clients systems</li><li>Deliver comprehensive status reports and critical solution updates to the team</li><li>Speak to customers to quickly get to the root of their problem</li><li>Proactively follow up with clients to ensure problem is addressed accurately and promptly</li><li>Collaborate with other groups (account managers, product managers, developers...)  when required to resolve issues requiring escalation</li><li>Build, develop and grow relationships with clients to establish mutual trust and provide a foundation for a strong working relationship</li><li>Write technical notes and troubleshooting procedures to be used internally and externally</li></ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul><li>BA/BS Degree</li><li>2+ years of experience in a technical support role</li><li>Strong hardware and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Ownership of an issue from initial reporting to properly documented conclusion</li><li>The ability to critically, and quickly analyze technical issues, with a highly structured work approach and the ability to manage multiple activities in parallel</li><li>Demonstrated success in Technical Support roles working with complex software and high client volume</li><li>Experience at a loyalty platform or SaaS expertise - a plus</li><li>Experience with computer hardware, software, installation and configuration</li><li>Effective communication, presentation and interpersonal skills, including the ability to accurately analyze problems, explain solutions, and present technical information to end-users in a non-technical manner</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Perks!</strong></p><p>Unlimited PTO, monthly mobile stipend, home office stipend, 401K, FSA/HSA, hybrid or remote work schedule, Blue Cross Blue Shield insurance coverage, paternity and maternity leave, pre-tax commuter programs and more.</p>\n"
