        "description": "<p>We are looking for a technical product manager to complement our product management team and take responsibility for AIRA, our Artificial Intelligence Review Assistant.</p>\n<p>AIRA is arguably the most advanced AI product within the scientific publishing and is regularly featured in news outlets, such as IEEE Spectrum and the New York Times (see <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://spectrum.ieee.org/peer-review-of-scholarly-research-gets-an-ai-boost\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://spectrum.ieee.org/peer-review-of-scholarly...</a> and <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/23/science/conflict-of-interest-ai.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/23/science/conflic...</a>)</p>\n<p>We are currently seeking an enthusiastic team player with great initiative and a get-it-done attitude to drive the next evolution of AIRA and related tools. The selected candidate should be able to operate in a fast-paced work environment, while juggling several different tasks at the same time. Excellent organizational and communications skills are a must.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Key responsibilities </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create, maintain and prioritize AIRA's roadmap;</li>\n<li>Align the product vision and roadmap to market and stakeholder requirements;</li>\n<li>Daily interact with our Data Science team to ensure that their cutting-edge algorithms are embedded in AIRA's releases</li>\n<li>Take responsibility for AIRA's user experience and collaborate with designers, developers and stakeholders to create the outcome that adds most value based on the organization’s goals;</li>\n<li>Constantly communicate with all stakeholders in the appropriate language and abstraction level;</li>\n<li>Define, track and regularly report on KPIs and other metrics;</li>\n<li>Own the vision of the product, be responsible for the roadmap, communicate and work to secure the organization’s understanding and buy-in.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum three years as a product manager or similar position, ideally with a focus on web-based products;</li>\n<li>Strong analytical skills and independent, entrepreneurial, approach;</li>\n<li>Ability to build effective relationships through communication and transparency;</li>\n<li>Understanding of BPMN workflows engines, web technologies, databases and APIs;</li>\n<li>Experience with Agile Methodologies (SCRUM) is a plus;</li>\n<li>Experience in a strategic role in a Product Management department is a plus;</li>\n<li>Experience in the development of Digital Platforms or AI Products is a plus;</li>\n<li>Solid communication skills in English, both written and verbal are a must.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>25 annual leave days + 4 well-being days</li>\n<li>Participation in the annual company bonus scheme</li>\n<li>Flexible working framework and remote working opportunities across the United Kingdom</li>\n<li>Extensive learning opportunities through our Pluralsight and LinkedIn Learning partnership</li>\n<li>3 volunteer days through our online platform</li>\n<li>Access to Headspace app</li>\n<li>Online Yoga classes</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>How to apply</strong></p>\n<p>Please submit your application in English.</p>\n<p>The candidate must be an UK citizen or have a valid UK work permit. Our office is located in London, however remote working options are available within the UK. If you are interested, do not hesitate to apply online!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Frontiers actively embraces diversity and is a safe and welcoming workplace. Recruitment is free from discrimination including based on race, national or ethnic origin, age, religion, disability, sex, gender identity or sexual orientation. With over 600 employees from more than 50 different nations, our diversity creates vibrant teams and constantly challenges us to appreciate multiple perspectives.</em></p>\n"
