        "description": "<div class=\"h3\">Job Description</div>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vitalsource.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>VitalSource</strong><strong>®</strong><strong>,</strong></a> is hiring for a <strong>Senior Software Engineer </strong>to contribute to our <strong>Engineering </strong>team working 100% remotely or from our Boston, MA office.</p>\n<p>Acrobatiq helps students learn more, faster through tailored practice and immediate feedback in an engaging learning platform.  We also provide educators and institutions with advanced analytics and insights on how well their student are learning, leading to improved student engagement and academic achievement.  This is an exciting opportunity to help design, develop and implement features for educational applications used by millions of users globally.</p>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A dynamic, continually growing company and culture where your contributions make a real difference and new ideas are always welcome<strong>. </strong></li>\n<li>Significant ownership and responsibility for the systems you develop.</li>\n<li>Fast, agile development within a smart, highly collaborative, and dedicated team.</li>\n<li>Cutting edge, open-source tech stacks and large-scale, global applications that have a massive positive impact on students, classrooms, and institutions of higher learning.</li>\n<li>A competitive compensation package with generous benefits.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience</li>\n<li>5+ years of application developer/software engineer experience</li>\n<li>5+ years of experience with Python and related web frameworks</li>\n<li> 2+ years of experience with the Django framework</li>\n<li>Experience with MySQL or other relational databases</li>\n<li>Experience with Git or other source code control systems</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience developing large-scale, high availability web applications and RESTful APIs</li>\n<li>Familiarity with MongoDB or another NoSQL document database</li>\n<li>Proven ability to interface with product management and communicate across engineering teams; Ability to seek and provide guidance when needed</li>\n<li>A passion for open source-based development, continuous delivery models, and using best-of-breed tools</li>\n<li>Experience with Linux, Kubernetes, Docker, Redis, Pub/Sub, Celery, and/or other related platform technologies</li>\n<li>Ability and eagerness to learn new technologies and architectures</li>\n<li>Experience building and operating observable applications with APM, monitoring, alerting, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop creative and innovative solutions for the next generation of educational learning</li>\n<li>Participate in all aspects of the application development life cycle including specifications, prototypes, development, quality assurance, deployment, and operations</li>\n<li>Contribute thought leadership to software architecture and design discussions</li>\n<li>Develop and modify internal and external facing software as part of an engineering team</li>\n<li>Participate in team code reviews, presenting your work for feedback and providing constructive feedback to others</li>\n<li>Support development with appropriate documentation of your work</li>\n<li>Test your work hands on and with automated tests; shepherd it through the quality assurance and release processes</li>\n<li>Support the on-call operations of the team, troubleshooting and resolving issues when they arise</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><br></p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Qualifications</div>\n<p><br><br></p>\n<div class=\"h3\">Additional Information</div>\n<p><strong>Perks/Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A highly competitive compensation package with generous benefits beginning first day of employment for Medical/Prescription Drug plans, HSA, Vision, Dental and Health Care FSA.\n<ul>\n<li>15 vacation days, 12 sick days accrued annually, 8 company holidays, and 3 personal days</li>\n<li>401K match, Life and AD&amp;D, Employee Assistant programs, Group Legal, &amp; more</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Paid parental leave to support current associates in balancing their professional and personal lives as their families begin and grow </li>\n<li>Encouraged continued education with our tuition reimbursement program</li>\n<li>Take breaks or brainstorm in our game room with ping pong &amp; foosball</li>\n<li>Casual Dress Code &amp; Flexible Schedules (per team)</li>\n<li>Flexible Work Schedules (by team)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>VitalSource Technologies LLC</strong>, is the leading education technology solutions provider committed to helping partners create, deliver, and distribute affordable, accessible, and impactful learning experiences worldwide. As a recognized innovator in the digital course materials market, VitalSource is best known for partnering with more than 1,000 publishers and resellers to deliver extraordinary learning experiences to millions of active users globally—and today we’re also powering new, cutting-edge technologies designed to optimize teaching and learning for maximum results. Learn more at <a href=\"https://get.vitalsource.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://get.vitalsource.com</a> and follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/vitalsource\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/vitalsource-technologies\" rel=\"nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, and <a href=\"http://instagram.com/vitalsource\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a>.</p>\n"
