        "candidate_required_location": "USA Only",
        "salary": "",
        "description": "<p>VetsEZ (Veterans EZ Info, Inc.), a verified Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business (SDVOSB), is a leading provider of information technology services to commercial and government markets. VetsEZ is a company of Subject Matter Experts with deep expertise in Healthcare IT and Benefits Delivery. VetsEZ strongly believes in making complexity EZ by providing tangible solutions that improve day-to-day business transactions, maximize efficiencies, eliminate risks, and reduce our clients' costs. For more information, visit us at <a href=\"http://www.vetsez.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.vetsez.com</a>.</p>\n<p>We are currently looking for a remote <strong>VistA</strong> <strong>Test Engineer</strong><strong> </strong>for a position supporting a major federal project. The VistA Test Engineer will work in a fast-paced, SAFe Agile environment and participate in the entire system lifecycle, including analysis, planning, development, implementation, testing, documentation, and operations. An ideal candidate will have a combination of testing and technical knowledge within the VistA software that involves financial transactions.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use of FileMan in the testing process is required. This includes but is not limited to use of the Data Dictionary and Inquire lookups to validate testing results.</li>\n<li>The tester preferably has experience and knowledge of Integrated Billing and Accounts Receivable functionality.</li>\n<li>Experience analyzing technical customer requirements supporting design and VistA application development.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills and experience working closely in developer huddles to analyze scope and create test scripts, cases, and data for functionality planned within a build.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of testing enhancements, conducting regression testing and logging/resolving defects as they arise.</li>\n<li>Works well with multiple deadlines and changing priorities during the development lifecycle.</li>\n<li>The candidate should have skill in testing scenarios and cases and documenting the results in an accurate and timely manner</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or a related degree is required.</li>\n<li>4-7 years of relevant testing experience. </li>\n<li>Must have experience testing VistA applications, preferably Integrated Billing and Accounts Receivable.</li>\n<li>Knowledge and technical experience with VA and VistA architecture.</li>\n<li>Experience working with knowledgeable, key stakeholders and preferably has familiarity with Rally and JIRA Test Artifacts Repository Tools.</li>\n<li>Knowledge and experience with tools for Agile and DevSecOps.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Additional Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience in the VA or other health-related organization desired.</li>\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a multi-stakeholder environment.</li>\n<li>Ability to obtain a Government clearance.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Medical/Dental/Vision</li>\n<li>401k with Employer Match </li>\n<li>PTO + Federal Holidays  </li>\n<li>Corporate Laptop </li>\n<li>Training opportunities  </li>\n<li>Remote Opportunity</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability, or protected veteran status.</p>\n<p>Sorry, we are unable to offer sponsorship at this time.</p>\n"
