        "description": "<p>We are looking for an experienced React Developer to join our team. The ideal candidate is highly self-motivated, proficient at transforming concepts into a solid architecture and requirements, meticulous and detail oriented, and able to quickly come up to speed on a large codebase. This is a full-time Canada wide opportunity with remote work allowed. </p>\n<p><strong>Duties/Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>     Driving platform technical design and build</li>\n<li>     Writing reusable, testable, and scalable code</li>\n<li>     Review and actively participate in architectural discussions</li>\n<li>     Works closely with development, integration and test teams to ensure product quality</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong> Skills:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>     Minimum 2 years professional experience with React</li>\n<li>     Experience developing against multiple APIs/Data Sources in a single application</li>\n<li>     Familiarity with Node.js helpful and/or GoLang helpful</li>\n<li>     Experience with Continuous Integration and Deployment pipelines for React applications also helpful</li>\n<li>     Excellent written, communication, interpersonal, and problem-solving skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with Agile/Scrum and Jira</li>\n<li>Experience with inclusive development and digital accessibility implementations (such as WCAG compliance)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>About Diamond</strong></p>\n<p>Diamond is a digital technology agency that defines and delivers technology innovation from idea to product, seamlessly fuelling the ever-evolving consumer experience. The Diamond team has decades of expertise in building web, software, mobile, and VR development projects for clients ranging from startups to Fortune 100 across many scales. We offer flexibility in work hours and remote opportunities, benefits, several perks, and a team-oriented environment built on trust and respect for others. Check us out on www.diamond.la</p>\n"
