        "description": "<div class=\"h2\">Description:</div>\n<p>Sparkbox is looking for a web designer with a passion for building a better web.​ We're always keeping our eyes out for great people—always looking, selectively hiring. The right person for this position loves collaboration with coworkers and clients and believes it brings about the best work. The right person also wants to work in a learning-hungry web environment and help lead the web industry by sharing.</p>\n<p>If you're right for this position, first and foremost you have stellar design skills and a portfolio to back it up. You feel right at home designing a visual language for a website and thinking about designing modularly for design systems. You care about the little details when it comes to typography, interactions, animations, user experience, and layout. You have a human-centered view of the web, know its limitations and possibilities, and care about performance.</p>\n<p><strong><em>This is a fully remote position.</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"h2\">Requirements:</div>\n<p>Passion and humility are vital, as you'll work directly with our designers, project managers, and other developers at Sparkbox. You'll also interact with clients and should feel comfortable presenting work. You'll need to be eager to learn new things, advance your skills, and push to find new processes.</p>\n<p>Experience and fluency in the latest web/design tools is required:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Figma</li>\n<li>Adobe Creative Suite (mainly Illustrator, Photoshop)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Not required but a bonus if you have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with animation/prototyping tools (Principle, Framer, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience with UX research and user testing</li>\n<li>Experience with writing some HTML/CSS</li>\n<li>3+ years of experience in UX/UI design</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"h1\">Inclusive Mindset</div>\n<p>Sparkbox has been intentionally working to build a team where we acknowledge our own imperfections, make all feel welcome, and humbly help each other grow. If you can bring a fresh perspective to a team of humble people who love what they do, we'd love to talk with you.</p>\n<div class=\"h1\">Benefits</div>\n<p>In return for your outstanding work, Sparkbox offers the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remote work</li>\n<li>Flexible Schedule</li>\n<li>Competitive Salary</li>\n<li>Healthcare Insurance</li>\n<li>Vision Insurance</li>\n<li>Dental Insurance</li>\n<li>Mental Health Sessions (Employer Paid)</li>\n<li>Accident, Critical Illness &amp; Hospital Insurance</li>\n<li>Health Savings Account (Employer Match)</li>\n<li>Flex Savings Account</li>\n<li>Simple IRA (Employer Match)</li>\n<li>Paid Vacation</li>\n<li>Vacation-Buy Option</li>\n<li>Annual Vacation Bonus</li>\n<li>Annual Wellness Budget</li>\n<li>Annual Education Budget and Match</li>\n<li>Commission Opportunities</li>\n<li>Paid Holidays</li>\n<li>Short/Long-Term Disability</li>\n<li>Provided Equipment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>People and families come first around here, which is part of why we offer 13 paid holidays (including a week or more shutdown at the end of the year) in addition to vacation.</p>\n<p><em>It is the policy of Sparkbox to ensure equal employment opportunity without discrimination or harassment on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, marital status, citizenship, national origin, genetic information, or any other characteristic protected by law. Sparkbox prohibits any such discrimination or harassment.</em></p>\n<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong> We'll review and consider applications as they come in, so the sooner you apply, the better. Don't miss out!</p>\n<p><em>All applicants must be legally authorized to work in the U.S. to be considered. <em><em>Sparkbox is not registered for employment in CA, NY, or IL at this time. </em></em></em></p>\n"
