        "description": "<p><strong>Who we are:</strong></p>\n<p>ChartHop delivers a fresh take on People Analytics, bringing disparate sources of people data together in a dynamic platform that’s visual and actionable. Unlike legacy People Analytics solutions, ChartHop is designed to be used by the whole organization. This helps companies improve organizational health, drive alignment and accountability, and save time and money. </p>\n<p>ChartHop plays well with dozens of platforms through robust integrations across the HR tech stack, and serves companies like BetterCloud, Lightspeed, Starburst and InVision. ChartHop was founded in 2019 by Ian White and is backed by Andreessen Horowitz. <br><br>We’re looking for skilled and motivated people to join our team! Do you want to help companies unleash the power of their people data to plan effectively and with intention? Do you have what it takes to envision the future of work, and then to take us there? Join us!</p>\n<p><strong>Product Manager - Developer APIs</strong></p>\n<p>In this role you will collaborate closely with the Engineering, Design and GTM teams to build a best in class API for developers and industry partners. Together we will build an ecosystem of  applications that allow our customers to fully harness the power of ChartHop.</p>\n<p>This role reports into the VP of Engineering.</p>\n<p><strong>As a Product Manager, you will:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can think in terms of the big picture, but deliver on the details</li>\n<li>You are highly focussed on metrics (AARRRR) and obsess over that aha! Moment</li>\n<li>You care deeply about developer experience when building against APIs</li>\n<li>You can collaborate with other product leaders to align on a product roadmap that cohesively drives towards business goals</li>\n<li>You can balance the need for ease of use with Security and Scalability </li>\n<li>You do whatever it takes to make your product and team successful, whether that means writing a QA plan or hunting down the root cause of a user’s frustration</li>\n<li>You can turn incomplete, conflicting, or ambiguous inputs into solid action plans</li>\n<li>You communicate with empathy and exceptional precision</li>\n<li>You are technical enough to ask engineers good questions about architecture and product decisions alike</li>\n<li>Beyond just shipping new products, you obsess about continuous product improvement</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>5+ years product management experience</li>\n<li>Experience building and perfecting APIs at Scale</li>\n<li>Experience handling complex and/or sensitive data</li>\n<li>Experience working very closely with Engineering and UX teams to ship and iterate on products</li>\n<li>BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Engineering, Statistics or equivalent experience</li>\n<li>Curiosity and enthusiasm for talking to end users and understanding their world</li>\n<li>Recognized as a collaborative and influential leader; a great partner to all functions</li>\n<li>Strong track record of owning end-to-end initiatives and launching impactful products</li>\n<li>Exceptional product sense and strategic thinking</li>\n<li>Strong organizational and analytical skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Unsure if you meet the qualifications? We encourage Product professionals who are passionate about this work to apply!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Our Core Values:</strong></p>\n<p>We're building ChartHop to be the best People Software on the planet and that starts with hiring the best people globally. We’re building an inclusive culture we’re looking for people who embrace our core values: </p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Own it and share it:</strong> We believe transparency and accountability go hand in hand.</li>\n<li><strong>Design practically:</strong> We find elegant solutions to very complex problems.</li>\n<li><strong>Build for scalability:</strong> We’re here for the long haul, and we optimize accordingly.</li>\n<li><strong>Lead with empathy:</strong> We support each other, our customers and our community.</li>\n<li><strong>Secure above all:</strong> We protect our customers’ data like our lives depend on it. </li>\n<li><strong>Move intentionally:</strong> We move fast and we try not to break things. </li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Perks and Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Health/benefits coverage (Medical, Dental, Vision, Life insurance, Long term and Short term disability, many more) </li>\n<li>Work from home supplies stipend</li>\n<li>Professional development stipend</li>\n<li>20 Vacation days </li>\n<li>401K</li>\n<li>Parental leave</li>\n<li>Mental Health Benefits</li>\n<li>Many more</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>ChartHop is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, race, color, religion, national origin, disability, protected Veteran status, age, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.</p>\n"
