        "description": "<p>Speak4 is a technology start-up that makes it simple for organizations to empower their supporters to speak up for the causes they believe in via an innovative, frictionless digital advocacy platform. Speak4 was created by a team of experienced marketers, skilled technologists and award-winning digital strategists who wanted a better tool to help organizations mobilize grassroots support online.</p>\n<p>We are looking for a PHP Developer who is dedicated to the craft, writes code that they are proud of and can hit the ground running. A PHP Developer writes beautiful, fast PHP to a high standard, in a timely and scalable way that improves the code-base of our products in meaningful ways. You will be a part of a creative team that is responsible for all aspects of the ongoing software development from the initial specification, through to developing, testing and launching.</p>\n<p>Success in this role requires taking direction from the Chief Technology Officer and assisting with all aspects of the company’s product development. Ideal candidates will have top-notch experience with PHP, web development skills, be detail-oriented and take an entrepreneurial approach to their responsibilities.</p>\n<p>As one of the early members of our team, you will have numerous opportunities to expand your responsibilities and contribute to the company's product roadmap and future growth.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities and Essential Functions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have experience with PHP and SQL</li>\n<li>Write “clean”, well-designed code</li>\n<li>Produce detailed specifications</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot, test and maintain the core product software and databases to ensure strong optimization and functionality</li>\n<li>Contribute in all phases of the development lifecycle</li>\n<li>Follow industry best practices</li>\n<li>Develop and deploy new features to facilitate related procedures and tools if necessary</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3-5+ years of PHP experience</li>\n<li>Demonstrable knowledge of web technologies including HTML, CSS, Javascript, AJAX etc</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of relational databases, version control tools and of developing web services</li>\n<li>Experience in common third-party APIs (Google, Facebook, Ebay etc)</li>\n<li>Passion for best design and coding practices and a desire to develop new bold ideas</li>\n<li>BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related subject</li>\n<li>Proven software development experience in PHP</li>\n<li>Understanding of open source projects like Joomla, Drupal, Wikis, osCommerce, etc</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p>We offer competitive compensation with opportunity for a year-end bonus, medical, dental, vision, and life insurance. We also offer a paid maternity leave program and paid vacation and sick leave.</p>\n<p>Speak4 is an Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) employer.</p>\n"
