        "description": "<p>Consumers within the global iGaming industry are inundated with online casinos and sportsbooks to choose from, and often make decisions based on very little information being available; leaving them open to bad user experiences.</p>\n<p>At KaFe Rocks we aim to be THE lighthouse for reputable iGaming - shining a light on the industry and providing our users with valuable products, localised content, and data that will help inform their decisions.</p>\n<p>With a <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://kafe.rocks/values/\" rel=\"nofollow\">set of core values</a> that our Rocketeers live by every day, guiding us further on our journey as one of the leading iGaming affiliates, we really believe we can make a difference to our users’ experiences of this industry.</p>\n<p>We are a remote working company, with an HQ based in Malta. We have an entrepreneurial, ambitious and driven mindset flowing through the company and we will continue to push forward, growing organically within both current and new markets.</p>\n<p>As our team of Rocketeers continues to grow, we are searching for a Software Engineer in Test who will actively contribute to and review the design and code quality of our product. You will be building test automation at all levels, focusing on testability, efficiency, reliability and reusability.</p>\n<p>You’ll work closely with other tech team members and ensure automation coverage. You won’t mind getting stuck in and being hands-on when it comes to learning new methods and developing tests for new features as well as reworking existing code.</p>\n<p>If you share our vision of helping users make the best informed decisions, would like to grow your professional skill set, and want to work with our incredible team of Rocketeers, then we’d love to hear from you.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Your key tasks:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify testing requirements and create test specifications and test plan documents</li>\n<li>Design test scenarios and propose an understanding of the end-solution</li>\n<li>Knowing and using design patterns where appropriate.</li>\n<li>Setting up the infrastructure to run tests: tests in CI/CD, parallel.</li>\n<li>Configure automated tests to execute reliably and efficiently in CI/CD environment</li>\n<li>Automate external quality assurance tests necessary for SEO, Security and Reliability</li>\n<li>Develop automated test cases and scripts to create a test automation framework</li>\n<li>Create environments and write integration, system, acceptance, load, performance and stress tests</li>\n<li>Regularly implement functional and exploratory testings</li>\n<li>Create &amp; manage bug reports and communicate with the team</li>\n<li>Collaborate with software engineers and assist with debugging</li>\n<li>Actively improve the overall design, testability, and quality of the tests</li>\n<li>Be the gatekeeper of quality and the driver of automating processes</li>\n<li>Enforce the quality mindset in the team, by providing support on developers to test their code</li>\n<li>Developing tools to assist manual and exploratory testing</li>\n<li>Regularly monitor and measure our code quality metrics and technical debt</li>\n<li>Communicate with Product Managers and Software Engineers to ensure qualitative delivery aligned with correct requirements</li>\n<li>Have a proactive approach to learning, growth, and sharing</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or a similar field</li>\n<li>5+ years of software engineering experience in Test Automation, Test Tooling and Infrastructure, and Development Deployment Operations.</li>\n<li>3+ Experience in PHP and/or JavaScript frameworks</li>\n<li>Knowledge of test methodologies, principles and guidelines</li>\n<li>Exposure to Behaviour Driven Development and understanding of object oriented programming</li>\n<li>Experience of working \"AGILE + DevOps\" process management methodology.</li>\n<li>Extensive knowledge of Cypress, Selenium, Postman, Jmeter, Cucumber</li>\n<li>Experience using scripting languages (PHP, Python, Bash)</li>\n<li>Knowledge of code versioning tools</li>\n<li>Experience working with debugging tools</li>\n<li>Good understanding of website architecture and aesthetics</li>\n<li>Good understanding on Search Engine Optimization(SEO)</li>\n<li>Self-motivated and highly organized</li>\n<li>Have a passion for quality, automation and ability to recognize risks and errors</li>\n<li>Ability to balance multiple projects simultaneously</li>\n<li>Strong communication skills (preferably in English and a second language)</li>\n<li>A high work ethic with the drive to get things done</li>\n<li>iGaming, gaming and/or affiliate experience is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A company that <strong>truly values its employees</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Remote working &amp; a brand-new office</strong> in Malta called \"<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://kafe.rocks/about/#oasis\" rel=\"nofollow\">Oasis</a>\"</li>\n<li><strong>Flexible working hours</strong></li>\n<li>Relocation package if you move to Malta</li>\n<li><strong>Competitive salary</strong> based on your experience</li>\n<li>A genuine<strong> opportunity to progress and develop</strong> further</li>\n<li><strong>Educational Bi-Fridays</strong>: Every other Friday, the leadership Team presents different topics to fuel learning &amp; development</li>\n<li><strong>Annual Reunion</strong> in a tropical place</li>\n<li><strong>Annual Team Round-ups</strong> in the location of the teams choice</li>\n</ul>\n<p>At KaFe Rocks Group diversity, equity, and inclusion are at the core of who we are. Our commitment to these values is unwavering. Together, we continue to build an inclusive culture that encourages, supports, and celebrates the diverse voices of our employees. It fuels our innovation and connects us closer to our customers and the communities we serve.</p>\n"
