        "description": "<div class=\"h3\">OUR SOLUTION</div>\n<p>Demyst unlocks innovation with the power of data. Our platform helps enterprises solve strategic use cases, including lending, risk, digital origination, and automation, by harnessing the power and agility of the external data universe. We are known for harnessing rich, relevant, integrated, linked data to deliver real value in production. We operate as a distributed team in the US and Asia and serve over 50 clients globally as a strategic external data partner. Frictionless external data adoption within tech forward enterprises is unlocking market growth and allowing solutions to finally get out of the lab. If you like to actually get things done and deployed, versus never ending exploration, Demyst is your new home.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h3\">The Challenge</div>\n<p>As an AWS Cloud Solutions Architect for Demyst you will be a member of a global team that is responsible for the architecture and implementation of Demyst's AWS Cloud Solutions. Your work will evolve, modernize and automate a highly available, secure and distributed system that spans multiple AWS accounts and regions. Our APIs host some of the largest banks real-time data needs, so a deep understanding of AWS, Big Data Solutions, DevSecOps is required. This is a unique opportunity to work with a team that is disrupting and revolutionizing the way enterprise organizations find the signal in the noise of big data.</p>\n<p>If you see AWS not as a cloud infrastructure provider but as a collection of 285+ software services that can be integrated together to provide modern, cloud native solutions then we definitely want to talk to you.</p>\n<p>Candidates must be located in the US-West Coast due to timezone needs. Position is fully remote.</p>\n<div class=\"h3\"> </div>\n<div class=\"h3\">Responsibilities</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Support Technical Sales Calls and translate customer needs into solution design</li>\n<li>Create Diagrams of solutions following AWS Well Architected Best practices using an AWS integrated diagram tool</li>\n<li>Create CI/CD pipelines as code to deploy entire solution, leveraging AWS DevOps tooling and automating Build, Test and Deploy stages</li>\n<li>Create infrastructure as code using Cloudformation and Terraform to deploy infrastructure stack across multiple accounts and regions</li>\n<li>Lead assigned projects/initiatives from concept to optimization</li>\n<li>Perform Incident Management, problem management and root cause analysis to restore services and implement enhancements</li>\n<li>Maintain AWS knowledge and achieve target certifications as agreed upon with management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 5+ years experience with AWS.</li>\n<li>Experience supporting pre-sales technical discussions and translating customer needs into Cloud native solutions.</li>\n<li>Experience Architecting, Diagraming and Implementing AWS cloud native solutions.</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS Diagraming tools such as LucidChart, CloudCraft, Gliffy or <a class=\"external\" href=\"http://Hava.io\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hava.io</a>.</li>\n<li>Experience working with multi account/multi region deployments utilizing AWS Organization and AWS Well Architected framework.</li>\n<li>Experience working as a member of a DevSecOps team following Scrum.</li>\n<li>Extensive experience with infrastructure as code / CloudFormation and Terraform. Should be able to understand, develop and deploy templates from day 1.</li>\n<li>Hands-on knowledge of AWS Networking such as how to deploy VPCs, private and public Subnets in a multi AZ deployment, allocate appropriate CIDR blocks, configure Route Tables, configure Security Groups, NACLs, Service Endpoints, establish hub and spoke connectivity via transit gateways.</li>\n<li>In depth knowledge of AWS IAM, cross account access, Role based access, writing and understanding of IAM policies, S3 bucket policies, VPC endpoint policies, and Service Control Policies.</li>\n<li>Working experience building CI/CD pipelines and automating deployments for and management of server-based, container-based and serverless architectures in AWS. (EC2, ECS and EKS on EC2 and Fargate, Cognito, S3, API Gateway, Lambda, Dynamodb, Docker Hub and AWS ECR).</li>\n<li>Extensive experience following GitOps / DevSecOps practices using GitHub, GitHub Actions, AWS CodeBuild, CodePipeline and CodeDeploy to manage all AWS resources and deployments.</li>\n<li>Experience with Internet Gateway, NAT Gateway, Application Load Balancers, CloudFront, Route53 and Auto Scaling Groups and how to route/protect traffic to and from AWS resources to the public internet.</li>\n<li>Minimum of AWS Solutions Architect Associate or AWS Developer Associate certifications.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"h3\"> </div>\n<div class=\"h3\">Preferred Requirements</div>\n<ul>\n<li>10+ years experience with AWS</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS Config, CloudWatch, CloudTrail, X-Ray and EventBridge on a multi account/multi region deployment to enhance and automate observability.</li>\n<li>Experience with creating/deploying automated tests throughout the CI/CD pipeline (static analysis, vulnerability analysis, Unit, Functional, Regression, Integration, Load/Performance, cross-browser testing)</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS Security portfolio of services such as Secret Manager, AWS KMS, AWS Macie, Amazon Inspector, AWS WAF, AWS Shield and AWS GuardDuty.</li>\n<li>Experience with Node.JS, Python and Bash scripts.</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS Image Builder and/or Terraform Packer for AMI lifecycle management in a multi account/ multi region setup.</li>\n<li>Experience deploying and managing EMR clusters.</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS RDS deployments (Aurora, PostgreSQL, MySQL).</li>\n<li>Experience configuring and integrating external identity providers such as Onelogin with AWS SSO in a multi account / multi region deployment.</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS Service Catalog and deployment of self-service products / Account Factory for creation of multiple AWS accounts and standard product deployments.</li>\n<li>Experience working with large financial institutions or other large enterprises in a regulated industry.</li>\n<li>One of the following AWS Pro certifications - Solutions Architect Professional or DevOps Engineer Professional.</li>\n<li>One of the following AWS Specialty certifications - AWS Security Specialty, AWS Advanced Networking Specialty AWS Database Specialty or AWS Data Analytics specialty.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with the largest consumer and business external data market in an emerging industry that is fueling AI globally</li>\n<li>Outsized impact in a small but rapidly growing team offering real autonomy and responsibility for client outcomes</li>\n<li>Stretch yourself to help define and support something entirely new that will impact billions</li>\n<li>Work within a strong, tight-knit team of subject matter experts and overseeing a team of renaissance technical talent</li>\n<li>Small enough where you matter, big enough to have the support to deliver what you promise</li>\n<li>Distributed working team and culture, recognition of outcomes and merit, not presenteeism</li>\n<li>Generous benefits &amp; competitive compensation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Demyst is committed to creating a diverse, rewarding career environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We strongly encourage individuals from all walks of life to apply.</em></p>\n"
