        "description": "<div class=\"h1\"><strong>Overview - Why Stack Overflow?</strong></div>\n<p><span style='\"font-weight:'>85% of the world's developers use Stack Overflow. Why is this important to you? Every app on your cell phone, your computer, in your car, on your TV, and in your refrigerator was very likely influenced by a developer who uses our platform. In the same way all Accountants use MS Excel, all developers us Stack Overflow. </span></p>\n<p><span style='\"font-weight:'><strong>Stack Overflow</strong> is the largest, most trusted online community for developers to learn, share their knowledge, and build their careers. More than <strong>100 million</strong> professional and aspiring programmers visit Stack Overflow each month to help solve coding problems, develop new skills, and find job opportunities.We partner with businesses to help them understand, hire, engage, and enable the world's developers. The products and services are focused on technical recruiting, developer marketing, and enterprise knowledge sharing. Our clientele includes Google, Microsoft, Bloomberg, and many other Fortune 500 names.</span></p>\n<div class=\"h2\"><span style='\"font-weight:'><strong>Accounting Manager - Remote anywhere on earth and Mars someday soon. </strong></span></div>\n<p><span style='\"font-weight:'>As the </span><strong>Accounting Manager </strong><span style='\"font-weight:'>at Stack Overflow you’ll be responsible for all of the day to day accounting functions for our entities based in the US and Europe. You will also develop and manage systems, processes, policies and controls for these entities. The Accounting Manager, Operations plays an important role in ensuring the building blocks of our financial results, that is the daily financial transactions, are accurately recorded in the general ledger. You will also contribute to developing and mentoring our incredible Accounting Operations team. </span></p>\n<p><strong>What you’ll do:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Ensure all of the organization’s financial transactions - billing, collections, vendor payments, employee expense reimbursements, payroll and commissions - are accurately recorded in the financial systems on a timely basis</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Support the Accounting Closing team during the month-end close process</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Build new, improve existing and maximize the efficiency of our processes to lay the foundation we need to scale the business moving forward</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Build strong, collaborative relationships with key internal partners including the sales operations, procurement and people organizations</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Own the key systems related to the Accounts Receivable and Billing, Payroll and Vendor Payments functions</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Assist with the identification, selection and implementation of new system platforms</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Lead and develop your expert team to thrive and be challenged and continue to grow professionally</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Lead projects on our Finance roadmap from conception to completion</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Must haves:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Bachelor’s degree in accounting, or related field</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>CPA (or studying for the CPA exam) </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>2 –3 years experience as an Accounting Manager</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Strong organizational skills, detail oriented and the ability to multitask </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Energetic, highly organized and a self-starter with the ability to work independently and as part of a team<br></span><span style='\"font-weight:'>Ability to manage time-sensitive projects and collaborate with cross-functional teams </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Strong process management and internal controls skills</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nice to have:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Public accounting / private mix of experience</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Experience working in software/hi-tech industry with previous SaaS and Ad Tech  revenue experience highly preferred </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>SageIntacct ERP, Zuora, Expensify and Tipalti software experience </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Experience of running or managing payroll for 200+ people</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What you’ll get in return:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Competitive base salary </span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>20 days paid vacation</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Generous parental leave (12-16 weeks at 100% pay), family care leave, and unlimited sick days</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Stock options</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Completely free health insurance (no copay, no premiums)</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Gym membership reimbursement</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>Employees will never be poked with a sharp stick</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>If you want to work remotely…. We’ll reimburse you up to $2,000 to set up a great home office.</span></li>\n<li style='\"font-weight:'><span style='\"font-weight:'>If you want to work in our office… You’ll be in our headquarters in New York City, and enjoy additional benefits like free lunch every day prepared by our own in-house chefs, transportation reimbursement, and all the espresso you can drink.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Employment is conditioned upon successful completion of a background check and upon having the appropriate legal right to work.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Diverse teams build better products.</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><span style='\"font-weight:'>Legally, we need you to know this: </span></em></p>\n<p><span style='\"font-weight:'>Stack Exchange, Inc. does not discriminate in employment matters on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, national origin, age, military service eligibility, veteran status, sexual orientation, marital status, disability, or any other protected class. We support workplace diversity.</span></p>\n<p><em><span style='\"font-weight:'>But we want to add this:</span></em></p>\n<p><span style='\"font-weight:'>We strongly believe that diversity of experience contributes to a broader collective perspective that will consistently lead to a better company and better products. We are working hard to increase the diversity of our team wherever we can and we actively encourage everyone to consider becoming a part of it.<br><br></span></p>\n<div class=\"h6\">#LIRemote #BI-Remote</div>"
