        "description": "<p>We are looking for someone to help us with our documentation, our first role of this type, and an opportunity to write the playbook at an early-stage startup. Work with the RevOps founding team and help us execute on our path to helping builders worldwide understand the value of the RevOps platform through great documentation!</p><p>Why does the world need RevOps?</p><p>RevOps helps builders and operators break free from the agony of laborious closing tasks and empower their teams to win with templated proposals, approval workflows, pricing guardrails, and more. Centralize your Revenue Operations process and build the systems needed to help your GTM win.</p><p>RevOps lets growing businesses leave rigid CPQ (Configure, Price, Quote) systems behind with templated quotes, approval workflows, and pricing guardrails to empower their teams and help sales reps win. We are disrupting legacy solutions in a $2T market where many SaaS companies are still relying on Word docs and spreadsheets to manage a patchwork process. Productboard, Loom, and Onna are just a few of the companies that use RevOps to send smarter sales deals and close deals faster. </p><p>Technical Writing is a very important role and skill at RevOps because we're a product-led growth company. Driving discoverable value to users is our #1 priority. Documenting plays a key role in helping acquire, activate, and turn users into evangelists. </p><p>Up for the challenge?If you want to revolutionize the way company's scale their go-to-market, join us!</p><div class=\"h2\">About the Sr. Technical Writer position</div>\n<p>We are looking for a skilled Technical Writer who will produce high-quality documentation that contributes to the overall success of our products. You will work collaboratively with our product and revenue teams to make our products easier to configure and use.</p>\n<p>You should possess outstanding writing and presentational skills and be able to efficiently collaborate with your peers. We also expect you to have decent experience with IT systems and to be interested in learning something new. </p>\n<div class=\"h2\">Technical Writer responsibilities are:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Collaborate with internal teams to obtain an in-depth understanding of the product and the documentation requirements</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create high-quality documentation that meets applicable standards and is appropriate for its intended audience</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Write plain, detailed, and straightforward user interface text, online help, and developer guides</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Prepare tutorials to help end-users use a variety of applications</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Analyze existing and potential content, focusing on reuse and single-sourcing opportunities</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Develop and maintain the information architecture</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h2\">Technical Writer requirements are:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>2+ years' experience of working as a Technical Writer or other relevant position</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Significant experience in creating quality documentation with an attention to detail</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Strong ability to quickly grasp complex technical concepts and explain them</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Excellent written English skills</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Good practical experience with Microsoft Office</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Knowledge about the SDLC and software development</p>\n</li>\n<li>University degree in Computer Science, Engineering or other relevant areas</li>\n</ul>\n"
