        "description": "<p>Pixelmatters is a digital product design and development company.</p><p>Our <strong>mission</strong> is to create top-notch digital products that make people's life easier, everywhere, every day. Our <strong>vision</strong>  is to be a company in which people are proud of being, and for which  talented people look at a place they want to be, as a good reference.</p><p>We’re looking for you — a dynamic, autonomous, and experienced QA tester. A  team player who likes to work in a fast-paced agile environment.</p><p>Quality  is a core part of our process, we're always looking for ways to create  the best possible experiences on the projects we work on and it's  crucial to ensure that those experiences are delivered with the expected  quality. For this reason, we're looking to expand the QA team with an  experienced QA tester focused on mobile apps. <strong>And here is where you come in...</strong></p><p>Your  role will focus on validating product quality standards, relying on  careful observation, collaborate with developers to develop effective  strategies and test plans. It's also expected that some of these  validations are turned into automated tasks, towards the scalability of  the quality processes.</p><p>Some of your day-to-day tasks will include  UI  implementation validation, test features based on user stories,   implement regression testing strategies, and collaborating on QA team  strategy decisions.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul> <li>Bachelor’s degree in engineering, computer science or related field, or equivalent work experience</li> <li>Proven experience as a Quality Assurance Tester or similar role</li> <li>Experience in QA methodologies preferably focused on mobile applications testing (Android and iOS)</li> <li>Proficiency in reviewing and analyzing requirements, specifications, and technical documents</li> <li>Develop detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test plans and test cases</li> <li>Analytical thinking, with an eye on automation and efficiency</li> <li>Good understanding of English <i>and Portuguese</i> (written and spoken)</li> <li>Strong visual culture with a keen eye for detail</li> </ul><div class=\"h3\">It would be awesome if you also have...</div><ul> <li>Experience with automation testing frameworks</li> <li>Familiar with version control systems such as Git</li> <li>Proficient in handling multiple browsers, operating systems, and devices</li> </ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul> <li>Quality-driven, inspiring and collaborative work environment</li> <li>Competitive salary and benefits, including health insurance</li> <li>For now, you’ll be working fully remote. Over 2021, we’ve planned opening a new office located at Porto’s downtown. <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.pixelmatters.com/blog/remote-as-default-office-as-an-option-our-remote-work-approach\" rel=\"nofollow\">You’ll then be able to decide where to work from</a> </li> </ul>"
