        "publication_date": "2021-07-29T01:42:50.000Z",
        "candidate_required_location": "Western Hemisphere",
        "salary": "",
        "description": "<p>IO Global, creator of the Cardano blockchain platform, is searching for a Business Intelligence Analyst to join its Commercial team. We are looking for self-starting, curious people who enjoy working in a diverse team and for a fast-moving industry, and who enjoy working collaboratively with stakeholders to find innovative solutions to our customers' problems.</p>\n<p><strong>Your mission </strong></p>\n<p>Business intelligence analysts provide strategic insights to managers in IOG’s teams for effective business decision-making that aligns with the company’s mission and goals. The analysts focus on three areas: strategy and innovation, market research, and due diligence. Strategy and innovation research is forward-looking and examines myriad topics, including cutting-edge technology, from a macro level. Market research entails writing reports on markets, competitive analysis and more. Finally, due diligence involves examining potential partners and opportunities with a critical eye to avoid or limit legal, financial and reputational risk.</p>\n<p>As a Business Intelligence Analyst you will:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with product managers and other stakeholders to collect business requirements (project background, stakeholders, data, non-functional, interface, business glossary and definitions)</li>\n<li>Facilitate meetings, use brainstorming and consensus-building skills, and interact with executive-level project staff</li>\n<li>Facilitate workshops and mapping sessions with stakeholders</li>\n<li>Consult internal and external customers to bring solutions from the idea stage to delivery</li>\n<li>Build relationships with internal and external customers, act as a facilitator, and support functional areas within and outside IOG</li>\n<li>Convert business requirements into functional requirements and ensure they align with stakeholders (developers, testers, business stakeholders of the project)</li>\n<li>Work with testing and quality managers, and product owners to ensure all features are incorporated in the project test and QA plan</li>\n<li>Work with product managers, developers, marketing, and communication teams to deliver a high standard of user materials</li>\n<li>Identify target audiences for content.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Your expertise</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>At least 3 years of experience in business intelligence, consumer insights or market research</li>\n<li>Experience, interest in, and passion for blockchain would be a plus (please make us aware of any courses that you may have completed concerning blockchain)</li>\n<li>Must have experience in research report writing and chart building.</li>\n<li>Minimum of bachelor’s degree. Will consider those holding an associate’s degree or having some college experience subject to work experience and skill set.</li>\n<li>Preferably has experience in both primary and secondary research.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong></p>\n<p>IOG is a fully distributed organization and therefore this is a remote position. Due to team distribution we are ideally searching for someone in an American timezone.</p>\n<p><strong>All Colleagues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Flexible schedule</li>\n<li>Remote work - ability to work anywhere</li>\n<li>Laptop reimbursement</li>\n<li>New starter package to buy hardware essentials (headphones, monitor, etc)</li>\n<li>Udemy for Business</li>\n<li>Competitive PTO and Sick Leave plan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>US Employees</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Medical, Dental, and Vision benefits coverage through Anthem with 100% premium cost covered by IO Global for the employee and dependents</li>\n<li>Health Savings Account</li>\n<li>Life Insurance</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>UK Employees</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Monthly Health Stipend to use towards any wellness or medical coverage/service</li>\n<li>Pension</li>\n</ul>\n"
