        "description": "<div class=\"h1\"><strong>We are....</strong></div>\n<p>We are a cutting-edge e-commerce company developing products for our technological platform. Our creative, smart and dedicated teams pool their knowledge and experience to find the best solutions to meet project needs while maintaining sustainable and long-lasting results. How? By making sure that our teams thrive and develop professionally. Strong advocates of hiring top talent and letting them do what they do best, we strive to create a workplace that allows for an open, collaborative and respectful culture.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"h1\"><strong>What you will be doing....</strong></div>\n<p><em>We are searching for a data modeler to work on the analysis and documentation of database models as well as on improvements detection, troubleshooting of current data models and flows and data processing; which include the use of relational and NoSQL databases. You also need to be technically competent in order to understand systems and data flows and prioritize and work with developers while at the same time being comfortable allowing development teams to present solutions, while you are their knowledge base. Preferably located in Latam working remotely</em></p>\n<p><em>We are looking to recruit a talented and enthusiastic Data Modeler who will be doing the following</em><em>:</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Validate business data objects for accuracy and completeness.</li>\n<li>Evaluate data models and physical databases for variances and discrepancies.</li>\n<li>Develop and enforce best practices for standard naming conventions and coding practices to ensure consistency of data models.</li>\n<li>Optimize and update logical and physical data models to support new and existing projects.</li>\n<li>Identify the architecture and interfaces to data sources, tools supporting automated data loads, security concerns and data visualization.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"h1\"><strong>Knowledge and skills you need to have</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>2+ years of hands-on experience on:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Data modeling, SQL language and Transact-SQL.</li>\n<li>ETL tools.</li>\n<li>Data modeling tools.</li>\n<li>SQL Server databases.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Working knowledge &amp; understanding of technical language.</li>\n<li>Upper intermediate English level (writing and reading)</li>\n<li>Bachelor's degree in computer/data science technical or related experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"h1\"><strong>Bonus points for the following</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Database DevOps capabilities</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"h1\"><strong>Why choose us?</strong></div>\n<p>We will give you the opportunity to be the best version of yourself, develop professionally and create strong working relationships working remote or on site. While offering a competitive salary, we also invest in our people's professional development and want to see you grow and love what you do. We are dedicated to listening to our team's needs and are constantly working on creating an environment in which you can feel at home.... <strong>If this sounds like the place for you, contact us now! </strong></p>\n"
