        "description": "<p><strong><em>*Please note that although this position is marked as being in Japan - This is a fully remote position, and candidates should preferably be located in countries with timezones UTC +3 to UTC +6 to best be able to collaborate with the existing team.</em></strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://bitcoin.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bitcoin.com</a>'s mission is to create more 'economic freedom' in the world. By economic freedom we mean the ability for individuals to freely acquire and use personal resources however they choose. We assert that economic freedom is a fundamental human right and a vital component of human dignity, and we believe that it is foundational for peaceful and prosperous societies.</p>\n<p>Our vision is to provide the next billion people with access to products that exemplify the ideals of Bitcoin. These ideals - which include peer-to-peer transactions, decentralization, censorship resistance, and permissionless-ness - support economic freedom.</p>\n<p>Our approach is to develop and promote widely accessible products that support economic freedom. For example, our digital wallet - which has 16 million downloads - provides people with an easy-to-use, non-custodial method for buying, selling, storing, sending, receiving, and trading cryptocurrencies.</p>\n<p>We are seeking a talented Full stack Developer (front-end orientated) for <a class=\"external\" href=\"http://bitcoin.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bitcoin.com</a>, who shares our vision.</p>\n<p>The Full Stack Developer will work directly with the Games Development team and the Games Product Manager to improve upon the current games platform and future integrations.</p>\n<p>This is an unrivaled opportunity to work with a team of highly skilled product managers, developers, designers, clients and marketers to work on the next evolution of gaming with cryptocurrency.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Must-haves</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>3+ years experience with Javascript (out of which at least: 2+ Year Experience with either Python or Java, 2 years with ES6+) and NodeJS</li>\n<li>2+ years Experience with frontend frameworks (VueJS, ReactJS, or Angular)</li>\n<li>Experience working with Webpack</li>\n<li>Experience working with either SCSS, LESS or SASS.</li>\n<li>Familiar with Vuex or Redux</li>\n<li>Strong communication and collaboration skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>We'd also love if you have:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Proven experience with a large VueJS or React project</li>\n<li>Worked with game frameworks such as PixiJS or Phaser</li>\n<li>Experience with Docker</li>\n<li>Experience working in a Casino or games platform</li>\n<li>Experience working in a startup</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p>We are serious about what we do, but more importantly, we have a lot of fun doing it. Our work culture is modern, meaning we strive for work experiences based on transparency, productivity, trust, and passion. For all employees, benefits include:</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Flexible work hours</li>\n<li>Remote work</li>\n<li>Health insurance reimbursement</li>\n<li>Wellness program (gym, etc.)</li>\n<li>Japanese classes</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n"
