        "publication_date": "2021-07-24T13:40:36.000Z",
        "candidate_required_location": "UK Only",
        "salary": "",
        "description": "<div class=\"h1\">Information Security Manager </div>\n<p><strong>About Zappar</strong></p>\n<p>We are Zappar, the world's leading Augmented Reality platform and creative studio. It's our mission to democratize AR &amp; MR.</p>\n<p>During our decade in the industry, our Creative Studio team has built over a thousand AR experiences in partnership with some of the world's biggest brands. Our team has been pioneers in showcasing how AR technology can transform packaging, illuminate events and elevate marketing campaigns with innovative, engaging content.</p>\n<p>Our Augmented Reality development toolkit, ZapWorks, puts the power of AR in the hands of designers and developers. Targeting a wide range of business customers, from Learning &amp; Development teams at Fortune 500 companies, to some of the most innovative AR creative agencies across the world, our platform and suite of creative tools enables customers of all levels of technical and design abilities to push the boundaries of interactive creativity. </p>\n<p>We are also the proud creators of ZapBox, the first affordable, mixed reality kit that allows developers and businesses to reimagine how they design, build and create 3D experiences.</p>\n<p><strong>What you'll be doing:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Own and manage the cyber and information security governance lifecycle, including creation and gaining assurance of appropriate policies and standards</li>\n<li>Providing expertise and guidance on our internal processes and regulatory information security frameworks</li>\n<li>Leading and coordinating RFI/RFP responses whilst automating and improving processes to reduce time wastage</li>\n<li>Respond to information security questionnaires and queries raised by our clients and prospects</li>\n<li>Train the business on information security and best practices and manage our CybSafe programme</li>\n<li>Creating, reviewing and maintaining security policy, standards and procedures</li>\n<li>Reporting security status, events and recommendations to the management team</li>\n<li>Coordinating internal and external reviews for security frameworks</li>\n<li>Work with our Legal Counsel to review and agree information security provisions in client contracts and agreements</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>A few things about you:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>At least 2 years of experience in the Information Security field</li>\n<li>The ability to explain complex processes and technical concepts to a broad audience</li>\n<li>A good understanding of industry standard frameworks such as PCI-DSS, GDPR, Cyber Essentials and ISO27001</li>\n<li>Proven track record in managing and expediting complex RFI/RFPs with Fortune 500 businesses</li>\n<li>Ability to work independently within a defined remit, managing multiple objectives and stakeholders</li>\n<li>Excited by working in fast growth and highly adaptive environments</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Although these things would also be a bonus: </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience working with scale up tech and SaaS businesses</li>\n<li>Completed an ISO27001 certification process</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Other than the exciting work, any other pluses to working at Zappar?</strong></p>\n<p>While our Zappar family has got a lovely (dog-friendly!) office in beautiful, leafy Chiswick complete with shower facilities, bike storage and surrounded by some amazing shops, coffee shops and pubs, we run a ‘work where you work best' policy (UK only) so you can be fully remote if you wish. We operate flexible start and finish times to make life a bit easier for anyone who wants to spend time with their children, join an exercise class or just have a lie in!</p>\n<p>For those in the office, we have Friday drinks and we have a quarterly town hall where we all get together for updates on the company performance. Our socials have included tours of the Sipsmith's distillery and a team scavenger hunt across London. We truly are at the cutting edge of AR and have been recognized as one of Fast Company's ‘World's Most Innovative Companies'.</p>\n<p>We actively encourage underrepresented applicants: if you need any assistance or additional information with applying, please contact Shaun McInally-Buckley (Head of People).</p>\n<p> </p>\n"
