        "description": "<p><strong>About Us</strong></p><p><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://radar.io/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Radar</a> is connecting digital experiences to the physical world with a location platform for every app, every device, and every developer. We help enterprises like T-Mobile, American Eagle Outfitters, and Zappos increase engagement and improve operations, powering impactful location-based experiences for over 100 million end-users.<br></p><p>Our team has backgrounds at companies like Google Maps, Foursquare, and Facebook. We are backed by top investors including Accel and Two Sigma Ventures. We are currently 30 employees based out of Brooklyn.</p><p><strong>About the role</strong></p><p>Radar is looking for a Senior Product Designer with a passion for designing developer tools and creating scalable design systems. You’ll help drive the UI/UX for our web and mobile products that developers rely on to build location-aware app experiences.</p><p>As our second product design hire, you’ll get the chance to have lots of autonomy and impact. You’ll play a pivotal role in leading our design efforts, defining our product’s vision, strategy, and user experience; and building our design culture.</p><p>You will report to our Senior Director of Product.</p><p><strong>What you’ll do: </strong></p><ul> <li>Lead and ideate our products from scratch; improve our features</li> <li>Redesign our toolkit mobile app (iOS and Android), new products, and web pages</li> <li>Develop and expand our product design systems</li> <li>Collaborate with our product team, engineers, and cross-functional stakeholders to understand requirements, and provide creative, thoughtful solutions</li> <li>Communicate the user experience at various stages of the design process with wireframes, flow diagrams, storyboards, mockups, and/or high fidelity prototypes</li> <li>Integrate user feedback and business requirements into ongoing product experience updates</li> </ul><p><strong>You have: </strong></p><ul> <li>5+ years of product design (UI/UX) experience at a B2B SaaS company</li> <li>Experience designing developer-focused products</li> <li>Expert proficiency in Adobe Illustrator, Adobe After Effects, Sketch/Figma </li> <li>A strong portfolio showing usable digital interfaces with strong product and visual design <strong>(Please include URLs for an online portfolio. Applications without a portfolio included will not be considered</strong>)</li> <li>Experience with product animations and illustrations, a plus</li> <li>Strong prototyping and design demo experiences (ie. Framer), a plus</li> </ul><p><strong>You’ll work with:</strong></p><ul> <li> <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/charlenealee/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Charlene Lee</a>, Senior Director of Product</li> <li> <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholaspatrick/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nick Patrick</a>, CEO </li> <li> <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/berylw/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Beryl Wang</a>, Product Designer</li> <li>Our Software Engineering and Marketing Teams!</li> </ul><p><strong>Perks:</strong></p><ul> <li>Remote friendly</li> <li>Competitive compensation package and equity plan</li> <li>Medical, dental, and vision plans with 100% premiums covered for you</li> <li>401(k) plan with employer match</li> <li>Flexible work hours and vacation policy</li> </ul><p><em>We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender, gender identity or expression, or veteran status. We are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace.</em></p>"
