        "candidate_required_location": "Mexico",
        "salary": "",
        "description": "<div class=\"h1\">Description</div>\n<p>Our client represents the connected world, offering innovative and customer-centric information technology services and solutions, enabling Enterprises, Associates and the Society to Rise™. Our client is a USD 4.0 billion company with 107,100+ professionals across 90 countries, helping over 800 global customers including Fortune 500 companies. </p>\n<p>Its innovation platforms and reusable assets connect across a number of technologies to deliver tangible business value to its stakeholders. Our client is also amongst the Fab 50 companies in Asia as per the Forbes 2014 List.</p>\n<p>Our client is part of the USD 16.9 billion Group that employs more than 200,000 people in over 100 countries. The Group operates in the key industries that drive economic growth, enjoying a leadership position in tractors, utility vehicles, information technology, after-market and vacation ownership.</p>\n<p>We are currently searching for an <strong>AWS Cloud Automation – AWS CHEF</strong>:</p>\n<p>Responsibilities &amp; Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience deploying, maintaining and managing AWS based production and non-prod environment.</li>\n<li>Strong experience in Infrastructure provisioning tools  – CHEF is a must.</li>\n<li>Scripting and programming languages (Python, Ruby, Perl, PowerShell, Golang, etc.)</li>\n<li>Should have strong knowledge and experience in AWS Developer tool services (AWS codepipeline, AWS codecommit etc.)</li>\n<li>Proficiency in building Linux and Windows systems. </li>\n<li>Deep understanding and Experience in AWS Cloud infra and Services. </li>\n<li>Experience administering application servers, web servers, and databases (Jetty, Tomcat, WebSphere, Nginx, Mongrel, Microsoft IIS, Oracle, MySQL, MongoDB, etc.)</li>\n<li>Deep hands-on experience leading the design, development and deployment of business software at scale or current hands on technology infrastructure, network, compute, storage, and virtualization experience.</li>\n<li>Strong hands-on experience in AWS services such as Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2), Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3), Amazon Simple DB/RDS databases, AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) etc., Security Groups, Upgrading EBS Volume Types, take snapshot, create a custom AMI, Load Balancers and Health Checks, Cloud Watch EC2, Auto scaling Groups, Using IAM Roles with EC2.</li>\n<li>Worked on Identity Access Management (IAM) like AWS permissions, Roles, Policies, MFA authentication, User permissions and Groups.</li>\n<li>Establishing communication between web server and app server by adding appropriate security group with needed ports and adding redirection rules</li>\n<li>Updating configuration files in GitHub and artifactory .(instances are integrated with chef). </li>\n<li>Updating SSL certificates for internally faced URLs using GitHub and artifactory , so that there won’t be any overlap of files.</li>\n<li>Updating SSL certificates for externally faced URLs in WAF(incapsula) and on load balancer in AWS console.</li>\n<li>Worked on CI/CD tools Jenkins and GIT version control system for continuous smooth code release process.</li>\n<li>Configuring the distribution at the cloud front and Clearing cache at the cloud front.</li>\n<li>Creating the s3 buckets and folders. Uploading the files in S3 buckets which are helpful in accessing the objects using the cloud front.</li>\n<li>Good knowledge on Route 53, Domain name Registration (DNS). </li>\n<li>Created AMI images of critical ec2 instances as backup using AWS GUI. </li>\n<li>Setup and manage backup and recovery using snapshot, Utilize EBS to store persistent data and mitigate failure by using snapshots.</li>\n<li>Configuring IAM roles for EC2 instances and assigns them policies granting specific level access to S3 buckets.</li>\n<li>Creating S3 buckets and managing policies for S3 buckets and Utilized S3 buckets for storage and backup on AWS. </li>\n<li>Should have knowledge with SSO authentication using OIDC/SAML. </li>\n<li>Required strong System troubleshooting and problem solving. </li>\n<li>Proven experience with software development life cycle (SDLC) and agile methodologies required. </li>\n<li>Should have good communication skills to work with clients directly.</li>\n<li>Should have experience in managing Service Management life cycle handling incident, changes, problem and request fulfillment </li>\n<li>Strong sense of personal accountability regarding decision-making and supervising department teams. </li>\n<li>Experience working in a high-level collaborative environment and promoting a teamwork mentality. </li>\n<li>Should have strong experience in handling multiple customers and key business users. </li>\n<li>Should have good communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Language: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>English Advanced.</li>\n<li>Spanish Native.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work from home flexibility.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you meet these qualifications and are pursuing new challenges that focus on delivering innovative solutions that increase business value, we’d like to talk with you today. Come be a part of the action at Sequoia Connect. Explore all our job openings | Sequoia Career’s Page: <a href=\"https://www.sequoiags.com/careers/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.sequoiags.com/careers/</a>.</p>\n<p><br><br>Keywords: <br>AWS Cloud Automation – AWS CHEF, Python, PowerShell, AWS codepipeline, AWS codecommit, Jetty, Tomcat, Websphere, Oracle, MySQL, MongoDB</p>\n<div class=\"h1\">Requirements</div>\n<p>None</p>\n"
