        "description": "<p><strong>Product Manager</strong></p>\n<p>Location: Boston, MA or Remote<br><br>eCare Vault is looking to add an experienced Product Manager to our team. eCare Vault enables a privacy-complaint, interoperable bridge for care team collaboration across sites and systems.</p>\n<p>In the rapidly evolving hybrid delivery of care and services in Education and Public Health, enterprises and community agencies are in urgent need of digital transformation of workflows that support care team collaboration. </p>\n<p>The Product Manager will report to the CTO and will play a key role in defining, planning and delivering our product roadmap in line with our clients business requirements and eCare Vault's strategic priorities. </p>\n<p><strong>Core Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with the management team to define product strategy for eCare Vault and coordinate across the business development and technology teams to enable its success. </li>\n<li>Create, update, and maintain product roadmaps based on the product strategy. </li>\n<li>Define, document, and prioritize product features. </li>\n<li>Breakdown features into user stories and work with the delivery team to groom and prioritize Sprint backlogs. </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinate, organize and participate in User Acceptance Testing  </li>\n<li>Work with the customer success team to demo, explain and document product features for existing and prospective customers. </li>\n<li>Capture user requirements through organizing workflow discovery sessions with eCare Vault's customers. </li>\n<li>Talk with existing users to capture feedback, synthesize the data and drive decision making around features. </li>\n<li>Identify, capture, and report on key product metrics. </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide analysis of competing products and help drive feature prioritization. </li>\n<li>Work with eCare Vault's partners to make sure the product roadmap is aligned with partnership objectives. </li>\n<li>Work with the development team to provide estimates and to report progress on strategic objectives to the management team. </li>\n<li>Support marketing and business development activities including participation in customer facing demos and requirement workshops. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>You Have</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Prior experience in a Product Manager or Product Owner role in a start-up environment.</li>\n<li>Understanding of Agile (Scrum or Kanban) processes. </li>\n<li>Demonstrated success in defining and launching new products. </li>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English. </li>\n<li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent. </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to travel to meet with clients and team members as and when necessary. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Put you over the top</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Technology background or previous experience as a developer or QA analyst. </li>\n<li>Previous experience working in the US healthcare or education domains. </li>\n<li>Understanding of HIPAA, FERPA and other healthcare and education regulatory requirements. </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience of working in a remote and distributed team. </li>\n<li>Previous Project Management or Agile Delivery experience. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\n"
