        "description": "<p>We are one of the leading Rust &amp; Haskell consultancies in the fintech, blockchain and AI space, with a passion for Rust, Haskell and open source software. We are looking for a remote Rustacean to join our team.</p>\n<p>If you are excited about Rust, robust and clean software and are up for a new challenge, you’ve come to the right place! We have places for both senior and more junior developers!</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong Rust and system engineering skills</li>\n<li>Strong software engineering and architecture skills</li>\n<li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills</li>\n<li>Basic knowledge of security, concurrency, backend systems, system scaling and databases</li>\n<li>Version control (git)</li>\n<li>Strong verbal skills in English</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with blockchain, substrate, smart contracts and/or compilers is a bonus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Focus on learning and individual growth in Rust, Haskell and Computer Science</li>\n<li>Work with other great Rustaceans, Haskellers, open source contributors and computer scientists</li>\n<li>Interesting and challenging projects</li>\n<li>Talk with anyone in the organization, regardless of team</li>\n<li>Remote work</li>\n<li>Flexible working hours</li>\n<li>6 weeks of paid vacation</li>\n<li>Competitive salary</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We have a variety of projects to work on at any time, ranging from payment stacks to smart contracts and blockchain to open source libraries, DSLs and compilers. If you like Rust and challenging projects, MLabs is the place for you!</p>\n<p>If you are interested please apply now!</p>\n"
