        "description": "<p>Mantium is the security and safety platform for large language models and artificial general intelligence. Developers trust Mantium to protect, observe, debug, and add human controls to their AGI applications. With Mantium, organizations of all sizes can easily leverage the power of LLMs and quickly remediate issues when they do occur.</p>\n<p><strong>What We're Looking For:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Craft core messaging, sales enablement, and selling assets for Mantium products</li>\n<li>Create and maintain market intelligence against competitors and develop competitive battle cards</li>\n<li>Partner with Product Management and Engineering leadership to advocate and inform product strategy and roadmap</li>\n<li>Act as the ‘voice of the product' to Customers, Press, and Analysts</li>\n<li>5+ years experience in product marketing, technical marketing, developer relations or communities, or product management</li>\n<li>Strong quantitative ability, and excellent written and oral communication skills.</li>\n<li>You are a person that loves to write and can write across a broad spectrum.</li>\n<li>You like learning how to build things and resolving how best to demonstrate the benefits of the product. You've written JaveScript, Python, PHP, Node, C#, or Java code and have opinions on the different web frameworks. You've built things yourself, and you know what it's like to commit to a repo and ship a release.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>\n<p>The Product Marketing team at Mantium is responsible for all digital assets that make help our users understand what Mantium is and how it can be helpful to incorporate into their projects. The Product Marketing team plays an integral role in talking to and listening to customers, understanding their delights, needs, and frustrations; and using that to advise the product narrative.</p>\n<p><strong>Where?</strong></p>\n<p>This position will be remote in the US. No matter where you are based, you will experience a company that believes in small teams for maximum impact; seeks well-rounded talent to ensure a full perspective on our customers' experience, understands that this is a marathon, not a sprint; that continuously and purposefully builds an inclusive culture that empowers everyone to do their best work and be the best version of themselves.</p>\n<p><strong>About Us</strong></p>\n<p>Mantium makes it easier for LLM developers to get projects up and running by providing monitoring, logging, human in the loop, and prompt management. We are a venture-backed organization with leaders who have had successful cybersecurity and machine learning exits.</p>\n<p>Healthcare Insurance and Leave</p>\n<p>• Prescription Drug<br>• Dental<br>• Vision</p>\n<p>Financial Benefits</p>\n<p>• Short and Long Term Disability Insurance<br>• Life and Accidental Death &amp; Dismemberment Insurance</p>\n<p> </p>\n"
