        "description": "<p>About CasperLabs</p><p>CASPERLABS, the developer of the Casper Network, provides professional services and support for organizations building on the Casper network. Guided by open source principles, we are committed to supporting the next wave of blockchain adoption among businesses and providing developers with a reliable and secure framework to build private, public, and hybrid blockchain applications. Our team possesses deep enterprise technology experience, hailing from organizations including Google, Adobe, AWS, Dropbox, and Microsoft.</p><p>We are looking for a talented Technical Writer to join the CasperLabs Ecosystem team. In this position, you will assist with the growth and adoption of Casper's leading blockchain technology by curating and growing Casper's knowledge base and technical documentation. You will work directly with the development team who built the Casper Network, the community, and other documentation end-users and stakeholders. In addition, the role offers opportunities for growth by assisting with educational materials and presentations for enterprises, partners, and exchanges on projects looking to adopt, partner with, or build on the Casper Network. </p><p>Responsibilities</p><ul> <li>Manage and maintain open-source documentation repositories</li> <li>Gather and maintain internal documentation when applicable</li> <li>Collaborate with other documentation contributors by reviewing and merging updates</li> <li>Write documentation for new features after trying them out and learning from the development team</li> <li>Write step-by-step tutorials for new developers and non-technical users</li> <li>Manage documentation requests and the documentation backlog in an Agile manner</li> <li>Collaborate with team members and with the community to understand what needs to be documented, simplified, or further explained</li> <li>Maintain the knowledge base in a consistent and organized manner</li> <li>Analyze gaps and improve the documentation by doing competitive research and analyzing the user experience</li> </ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>Qualifications</p><ul> <li>Experience with Github and contributing to open-source projects</li> <li>Comfortable with command-line and Linux CLI tools</li> <li>Ability to test features to understand them and write about them</li> <li>Proficient with markup languages such as Markdown or reStructuredText</li> <li>Experience with crypto, blockchain, or fintech, or at least a strong interest to learn</li> <li>Previous programming experience in any language</li> <li>Enthusiastic about writing and editing documentation</li> <li>Excellent communication and teamwork skills</li> <li>A clear and concise writing style in English</li> <li>Great attention to detail</li> <li>Ability to thrive and stay organized in a fast-paced environment</li> </ul><p>Additional preferred qualifications</p><ul> <li>JavaScript/TypeScript programming experience</li> <li>Python programming experience</li> <li>Rust programming experience</li> <li>Previous experience in Agile teams</li> </ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul> <li>Fully remote, work from home environment</li> <li>Flexible working hours</li> <li>Paid Time-Off</li> <li>Periodic in-person offsites globally (travel permitting)</li> <li>Long-term incentive programs</li> <li>Continued education support</li> <li>Advancement opportunity</li> </ul>"
